@node Browsing Feeds, Thread Tracing, Commands, Commands
@section Browsing Feeds

@deffn Command ssb-browse-feed feed-id &optional limit
Fetch and display messages from the SSB feed @var{feed-id}.
@var{feed-id} is the full @code{@@<pubkey>=.ed25519} string.
@var{limit} defaults to @code{ssb-browse-limit}.

When called interactively, prompts for both the feed ID and the
message limit, with the current value of @code{ssb-browse-limit}
shown as the default.

The feed opens in an @code{ssb-feed-mode} buffer.  Key bindings:

@table @kbd
@item n
Move to the next message and display its content below.
@item p
Move to the previous message.
@item @key{RET}
Open the message at point in a window below.
@item t
Trace the tangle thread rooted at the message at point.
@end table
@end deffn

@deffn Command ssb-my-id
Display the local erlbutt node's own feed ID in the minibuffer.
@end deffn

@node Thread Tracing, , Browsing Feeds, Commands
@section Thread Tracing

@deffn Command ssb-show-thread
Show the tangle thread for the message at point.

When invoked from a feed buffer, opens the full thread rooted at
that message.  When invoked from inside a thread buffer, shows the
sub-thread descending from the current entry, using the stored tangle
root so backward references resolve correctly.

The thread opens in an @code{ssb-thread-mode} buffer.  Key bindings:

@table @kbd
@item n / p
Step through thread entries.
@item @key{RET}
Display the full text of the entry at point below.
@item t
Drill into the sub-thread at point.
@end table
@end deffn

@node Customization, , Commands, Top
@chapter Customization

All maxbutt options belong to the @code{maxbutt} customize group.
Access them with @kbd{M-x customize-group @key{RET} maxbutt @key{RET}}.

@menu
* User Options::
@end menu

@node User Options, , Customization, Customization
@section User Options

@defopt ssb-node
The Erlang node name of the running erlbutt instance, as a symbol.
Default: @code{erlbutt@@localhost}.

Must match the @option{-sname} used when starting the release.  Change
this if you run erlbutt under a different name or on a remote host.
@end defopt

@defopt ssb-browse-limit
Default number of messages fetched by @code{ssb-browse-feed}.
Default: @code{2000}.

Can be overridden on a per-invocation basis when calling
@code{ssb-browse-feed} interactively.
@end defopt

